---
import ClientReportLayout from '../../../layouts/ClientReportLayout.astro';
---

<ClientReportLayout title="SEO & Competitor Analysis" clientName="1st Home Maintenance">
<nav class="top-nav">
  <div class="container">
    <a href="/clients/zolley/" class="nav-brand">Brothers Automate</a>
    <a href="/clients/zolley/">&larr; Back to Overview</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-badge">SEO & Competitor Analysis</div>
    <h1>480 people search for your services every month.<br>You're <span class="highlight">not on page 1</span>.</h1>
    <p>Your site ranks for just 24 keywords total. Your closest national competitor ranks for 59,210. But here's the good news: the keywords you need have zero competition.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="gap-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">The Visibility Gap</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">You vs. The Competition</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">Here's how your online presence compares to the top handyman businesses competing for the same customers in Boca Raton.</p>

    <table class="comparison-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Metric</th>
          <th>You (1st Home Maintenance)</th>
          <th>Mr. Handyman (Top Competitor)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="metric-label">Ranked Keywords</td>
          <td class="you">24 <span class="gap-tag">2,467x behind</span></td>
          <td class="them">59,210</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="metric-label">Monthly Organic Traffic</td>
          <td class="you">~26 visits</td>
          <td class="them">~932,966 visits</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="metric-label">Traffic Value (Monthly)</td>
          <td class="you">$247</td>
          <td class="them">$500K+</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="metric-label">Google Maps Position</td>
          <td class="you">Not Listed (No GBP)</td>
          <td class="them">#1 (286 reviews, 4.9 stars)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="metric-label">Google Reviews</td>
          <td class="you">0 reviews</td>
          <td class="them">286 reviews</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="metric-label">Page-1 Rankings</td>
          <td class="you">0 keywords</td>
          <td class="them">Thousands</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="metric-label">Website Pages</td>
          <td class="you">6 pages</td>
          <td class="them">Hundreds of service + location pages</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="metric-label">Social Media Profiles</td>
          <td class="you">0 (None)</td>
          <td class="them">Facebook, Yelp, BBB, Google</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #64748b;"><strong>Local competitors also ahead of you:</strong> Handyman Boca Raton (49 reviews, 4.8 stars), Best Boca Raton Handyman (67 reviews, 4.7 stars, 30+ years in business), Tom & Son Handyman (71 reviews, 4.8 stars)</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="missing-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">What's Missing</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">6 Critical Gaps Holding You Back</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">Each of these gaps is costing you leads every single week.</p>

    <div class="missing-grid">
      <div class="missing-card">
        <h3><span class="status-dot red"></span> No Google Business Profile</h3>
        <p>You don't appear in Google Maps at all. When someone searches "handyman near me" in Boca Raton, you're invisible. Your competitors have 49-286 reviews and dominate the map pack.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="missing-card">
        <h3><span class="status-dot red"></span> No Service-Specific Pages</h3>
        <p>You have one generic "handyman-services" page. You need individual pages for plumbing repairs, electrical work, drywall, kitchen remodeling, bathroom repairs, and more. Each page = a new chance to rank.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="missing-card">
        <h3><span class="status-dot red"></span> No Location Pages</h3>
        <p>You serve Boca Raton, Delray Beach, and surrounding areas, but have zero location-specific pages. These are free traffic opportunities with zero keyword difficulty.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="missing-card">
        <h3><span class="status-dot red"></span> Zero Reviews Anywhere</h3>
        <p>No Google reviews, no Yelp reviews, no BBB listing, no Angi profile. Reviews are the #1 trust signal for local service businesses. Your competitors have hundreds.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="missing-card">
        <h3><span class="status-dot red"></span> No Blog or Content</h3>
        <p>No blog means no long-tail keyword coverage, no topical authority, and no reason for Google to crawl your site regularly. Your 6 pages can only rank for a handful of terms.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="missing-card">
        <h3><span class="status-dot amber"></span> Missing Meta Descriptions</h3>
        <p>Your About and Contact pages have no meta descriptions. Your contact page has a duplicate H1 tag. These are easy fixes that affect click-through rates from search results.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="opps-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">Keyword Opportunities</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The Best Keywords You're Not Ranking For</h2>
