</section>

<section class="demand-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">Market Demand</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">People Are Searching. They're Just Not Finding You.</h2>
    <div class="demand-cards">
      <div class="demand-card">
        <div class="big-number">480</div>
        <div class="label">monthly searches for "handyman boca raton"</div>
      </div>
      <div class="demand-card">
        <div class="big-number">$9.39</div>
        <div class="label">cost-per-click (shows high buyer intent)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="demand-card">
        <div class="big-number">KD 0</div>
        <div class="label">keyword difficulty (wide open opportunity)</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="text-align: center; color: #64748b; margin-top: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">Search demand for handyman services in Boca Raton is consistent year-round, with slight seasonal bumps. This is steady, reliable demand that translates directly to phone calls and booked jobs.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="takeaway-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="takeaway-box">
      <h3>What This All Means</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>You have a technically solid website</strong> (97/100 performance score) -- the foundation is there, it just needs more content and local optimization.</li>
        <li><strong>Your biggest competitors are beatable locally.</strong> Mr. Handyman is a national franchise. The real local competition (Best Boca Raton Handyman, Handyman Boca Raton) have modest review counts you can catch up to in 3-6 months.</li>
        <li><strong>Every target keyword has zero difficulty.</strong> This is extremely rare. It means you can realistically rank on page 1 for your core service keywords within weeks with the right content and GBP setup.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Maps is your #1 priority.</strong> Without a Google Business Profile, you're missing the most valuable real estate in local search. The map pack gets 40%+ of all clicks for local service searches.</li>
        <li><strong>More pages = more rankings.</strong> Going from 6 pages to 20+ service and location pages could 5-10x your keyword coverage and organic traffic.</li>
        <li><strong>Reviews are your trust gap.</strong> With zero reviews on any platform, potential customers have no social proof. Even 10-15 Google reviews would put you in the conversation.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section">
